RACE.FOOTNOTES: MR MEMPHIS was on the pace from the outset, dueled the runnerup to the sttetch then dug in gamely and edged away. TRIBUNAL LOVE contested the pace outside the winner, stayed on determinedly to the stretch then was outkicked. HAKUNUI stalked the top two to the second turn, was asked for more but finished evenly. SCRATCH ME got outsprinted to the backstretch, was off the rail on both turns and lacked a closing response. PACKRAT BRANT had no speed, was three wide throughout and came up empty. LONGFORD tracked the pace while saving ground but weakened in the final furlong. LUKE'S PLACE broke outward, was corrected but was wide throughout and not a factor.

FREE nominations closed Tuesday, August 29 with seventeen. Or by supplementary nomination of $150 each by closing time of entries. $200 to pass the entry box. Preference by total earnings in 2022-2023. Fie ld will be limited to ten starters. Three-Year-Olds 124 lbs.; Older 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: XTRAFINE XTINA had good speed, was dueling well clear of everyone except the runnerup after the trouble on the first turn, dug in gamely in the drive and edged away. FEATHER INTHE WIND attended the pace outside the winner, stayed on to the stretch then was an easy second. RED NOON RISING was carried out six wide when PEARL RIVER DELTA bore out on the first turn, chased thereafter and closed a gap. BETHEL RIDGE was forced out seven deep to the backstretch and lost any chance. GALWALKSINTOABAR was carried out on the first turn then was not a factor. HEART ON THE RUN was pushed out five wide to the backstretch and also was never a threat. PEARL RIVER DELTA bore out badly on the first turn then was always outrun.

ENTRY.NAME: Xtrafine Xtina
ENTRY.COMMENT: good speed, dueled inside, responded, edged clear late
